          <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Define the characteristics of the image</head>
          <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en"><p>The important characteristics of the image are
              the following: <list>
                <item>Layout elements (tables, graphics, ...)</item>
                <item>Script type (handwritten, Gothic script, Roman script, non-European)</item>
                <item>Mixed content (pre-printed documents with handwriting)</item>
              </list> These characteristics determine the method: <list>
                <item>If it's a clean printed text, a classic OCR engine would be enough</item>
                <item>In other cases, i.e. handwritten, old printed texts with blackletter (gothic)
                  scripts, or low quality scans, using a model is necessary.</item>
              </list></p>
            <p>If a model exists, or it works out of the box, or it needs to be retrained or adapted. Otherwise, you have to train a model
              from scratch.</p></desc>
          <desc xml:lang="en" type="terms">
            <term key="Modeling" source="Tadirah" type="activity"/>
          </desc>
        </event>
      </listEvent>
